theorem Topology.frontier_diff_subset_union_frontier
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    frontier (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ frontier A ∪ frontier B := by
  -- Rewrite the difference as an intersection with a complement.
  have h₁ :
      frontier (A ∩ Bᶜ : Set X) ⊆
        frontier A ∪ frontier (Bᶜ : Set X) :=
    Topology.frontier_inter_subset_union_frontier (A := A) (B := Bᶜ)
  -- Use the equality `frontier (Bᶜ) = frontier B`.
  have h₂ : frontier (Bᶜ : Set X) = frontier (B : Set X) :=
    (frontier_compl (A := B)).symm
  -- Combine the two facts to obtain the desired inclusion.
  intro x hx
  have hx' : x ∈ frontier A ∪ frontier (Bᶜ : Set X) := h₁ (by
    -- `A \ B` and `A ∩ Bᶜ` coincide.
    simpa [Set.diff_eq] using hx)
  cases hx' with
  | inl hA => exact Or.inl hA
  | inr hBcomp =>
      have hB : x ∈ frontier B := by
        simpa [h₂] using hBcomp
      exact Or.inr hB

theorem Topology.frontier_compl_swap {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    frontier (A : Set X) = frontier (Aᶜ) := by
  simpa using (frontier_compl (A := A)).symm
